name: Customer-Segmentation-using-K-Means
description: A Project aimed at dividing a customer base into distinct groups or segments based on their similarities and preferences. The K-Means algorithm is a popular unsupervised machine learning technique used for clustering data points. I have used a mall's data to find most potential customers for the business.

name: DistributedKNN
description: This project demonstrates a parallel implementation of the K-Means clustering algorithm using MPI (Message Passing Interface). The code utilizes the distributed computing capabilities of MPI to perform clustering on large datasets in a distributed manner, enabling faster processing and scalability.
